Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Quadratic Horndeski, selecting a branch for \[Psi]", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.97988613563181*^9, 3.979886162819168*^9}, 
   3.981622669666246*^9, {3.988774920333218*^9, 3.9887749225379457`*^9}, {
   3.989381178431554*^9, 3.989381185296832*^9}, 3.98948344089326*^9, {
   3.991995436371139*^9, 
   3.991995459560246*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8aa9a9f5-4726-4723-b867-\
50add5019607"],

Cell["\<\
In this section, we compute the monopole perturbation equations for a general \
quadratic Horndeski theory. To speed up the computation, we restrict to the \
region $A(r)>0$ and fix a branch for $\\psi\[CloseCurlyQuote](r)$ via the \
substitution rule psisquaredtoX. These assumptions can be relaxed at will by \
modifying psisquaredtoX and replacing AssumptionsApos with usualAssumptions, \
at the cost of significantly longer execution times (see the following \
section for the fully general treatment).\
\>", "Text",
